\par Anne:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 [His] idea [is] to create a record of \endash  he calls it \'93Pioneers of Social Research\'94 \endash 
where, in their own words, they describe their career, describe their professional biography, and indicate how that relates to their personal biography. In other words, a life history interview, a professional life history inter
view, for posterity.... He started off with, I think, what he called \'93qualitative research\'94, so there\rquote s quite a bank of them, and some of them you can pick up the transcripts, or maybe even the recordings themselves, on line, because it
\rquote s in association with the British Library. I think he\rquote s looking for funding for his second stage, for quantitative, which is where, I think you\rquote 
re the first of the quantitative researchers... Thank you, again, for agreeing. What I wanted to do, the first thing I wanted to do, was be very sure about your timetable today, and how long you wanted or felt you wanted to go on? }{\rtlch\fcs1 
