\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 No, not at all. I think I was the last generation, say, where that would be possible. 
And being in Cambridge at that time - Ph.D.s were still viewed by the older generation, especially in the arts and social sciences, as not really necessary. So it was never a problem. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
