\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 Yes. This was the classic age, of course, o
f the one-child family. What was really very strange was that when our own first child was born, my mother told me \endash  and she\rquote d never told me before \endash  that about a year and a half before she had me, she\rquote 
d had a child who had died at birth, a girl, and so I often wondered if that child had lived, I might never have existed! (LAUGHS) The one child policy! Yes! }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
