\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 No. I mean, there may have been, but that didn\rquote t affect
 me at all. No. More serious were the tensions within sociology between Glass on the one hand, and people who were part of the Glass project, like Asher Tropp, and David Lockwood, and then the other side of the Sociology Department, Donald McRae and Juliu
s Gould. And Bottomore was on the Glass side, yes. Yeah. So it was a very unhappy Department by then. The great days were passed \endash  I now see, looking back \endash 
 when Dahrendorf and Lockwood were there together. But I got to know David Lockwood quite well, though. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
