400 a year, and I was getting \'a3320 as a graduate student, so, well, it was an improvement, but not m
uch. But then I got this job I guess some time in the late spring or early summer. A couple of months later, when I was playing tennis, it had been increased to \'a3700! Oh! And so I\rquote 
d never felt so rich! So I had to write some lectures, and I decided that I could do this better than staying in this country, so I went off with my girlfriend, to Barcelona for a month. I wrote my first sociology lectures in Barcelona! (LAUGHS) }{
