\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 Oh, I think there is a clear continuity. All I would say is that even at the end of my time at Leicester \endash  1960 \endash 
 when I moved on to Cambridge, I still didn\rquote t have altogether well-formed ideas about what sociology ought to be like, or what sociolog
y ought to be doing. I mean, I was aware of tensions between my approach and the Elias and Neustadt approach. And could I just say here that although we had these disagreements, it never affected our personal relationships. I had very good personal relati
onships with Elias and Neustadt to the end. I found them, you know, very generous people. What was really sad was that they had these terrible quarrels at the end, and I found that very very sad indeed. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
