\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 She was. Initially she thought, [after a] period of active motherhood, she wouldn\rquote t. But after just a few months here, 
she was asked if she would step in and do some temporary teaching, I think at Worcester College, and then another of these \endash  [it was] sheer chance in this case \endash 
 I mean, it was a very horrible thing happened. A young woman who was the French don at St. Anne\rquote s College, had been working in the Taylorian Library, on St. Giles there \endash  the Modern Languages Library \endash 
 and nobody knows what happened. She must have been completely absorbed in what she was doing. She came straight out of the Library and walked into the road in front of a bus, and was killed instantly. And so this vacancy then came up at St. Anne\rquote 
s and my wife got it. So then, after less than two years, she was back working full-time. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
