\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 I did. As I said, I was very much interested in this French sociologie du travail group, and when I 
moved to Leicester, Neustadt spoke fluent French, and he had French contacts, and I went over to France quite a bit in those years, to meet up with people there. I used to go to Raymond Aron\rquote 
s seminars at the Sorbonne. I spoke French fairly fluently, but inaccurately, and with a very bad accent! But I persevered, but then when I married my wife, that ruined my French because I knew I was always getting, like, \'df
- - (beta double minus), and when we went to France, as we did a lot, she would always say, \'93Oh, let me do the talking\'94, because she could pass for French. She\rquote 
s Welsh, you see, she grew up partly in Wales, partly in Brittany, that kind of Celtic connection, and in those days, you were very likely to get ripped off in France anywhere, if they thought you were foreign, so she did the talking. I\rquote 
m afraid my spoken French really went down. I still speak it from time to time if I have to, but I still read it, I have no problem reading it, but [my] spoken French is not too good. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
