\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 Oh no, no. It\rquote s more - to simplify it, it\rquote 
s more the individualistic paradigm as opposed to the holistic paradigm, that you really begin with - or end might be a better way. But all explanations of social phenomena have, in the end, to be given in terms of individual action and interaction. It
\rquote s Popperian methodological individualism. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
\par 
\par Anne:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 So this is Weberian interaction, isn\rquote t it? It\rquote s ... the way Weber talks about action between people. So that\rquote 
s where agency arises. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
\par 
\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 Oh yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
\par 
\par Anne:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 But that\rquote s not the word that you used. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
