\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 Yes. This model is still used, and it\rquote 
s not only used, of course, in mobility, but Anthony Heath at that time, he had taken over the British Election Study - and it hadn\rquote t done very
 well, to be honest, in its time at Essex - and Anthony had worked in part, on the mobility project here, and he had learnt these techniques, and then they applied very well to the analysis of the relationship between class and vote. It was formally an id
e
ntical problem. So he really, with John Curtis and others, transformed electoral sociology by taking over these techniques of contingency table analysis So I think, in purely academic terms, that was the most generally important contribution, to get peopl
e
 to move away from thinking that regression analysis was the beginning and end all of data analysis in quantitative data analysis in sociology, and get back to the analysis of contingency tables where, if appropriate, you could use categorical data. This 
is very much in the tradition of Lazarsfeld, and as I became more interested in quantitative sociology, I became more and more interested in Lazarsfeld\rquote 
s work and a great admirer of Lazarsfeld. And I met him once, through Marie Jahoda, who had been married to him. An extraordinary man! But, of course, Lazarsfeld, again, didn\rquote 
t have these techniques. But you could do what Lazarsfeld was trying to do then, much more effectively using these techniques. Leo Goodman, has a wonderful image for this. He said, you know, \'93You\rquote 
ve to think of how the sculptor, before he begins, sees the angel in the block of marble, the block of stone\'94. I think, with these techniques, you begin with a big block of data, and you don\rquote t really know what\rquote 
s going on there, and you can use these techniques to see some very interesting shapes and patterns within the block of data. So I\rquote 
m very encouraged by the way in which this has moved on into a lot of other fields, like homogamy, for example, and it\rquote s still developing. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
\par 
\par Anne:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 Can I just break in, and say, do you feel proud of yourself? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
