\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 Oh yeah, it was Viking. Well, my name is - I mean, \'93torp\'94 is Viking for \'93little settlement\'94. And \'93Goldesthorpe\'94
 - it used to be spelt with an \'93S\'94 until the 19th century - Golda was some minor Viking chieftain, so \'93Goldas torp\'94 was \'93Golda\rquote s little village\'94. I grew up just three or four miles away from Goldthorpe, from the village. }{
