\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 Oh yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
\par 
\par Anne:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 I was just wondering about whether you\rquote re splitting it, so you\rquote re taking mothers\rquote  and fathers\rquote 
 income, education, etc., where you, presumably, have got at least four by four versions. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
\par 
\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 Yes. Yes. Yes. Well, actually, Wing, Tak Wing Chan is now working on this, on the three generation effect. The problem is, he\rquote 
s using the birth cohort studies, which are I suppose really the only good data source on this, and the problem is that the cohort studies lack data on what I think is the most crucial - probably
 the most crucial grandparental influence - and that is wealth \endash  the handing down of money to fund children\rquote s private education, or help the parents to buy houses near good State schools, pay for private tuition. So far, he\rquote 
s found some three-generation effects, but they\rquote re not very big. In fact, there\rquote s a body of research that suggests they don\rquote t exist. He\rquote s been very critical of that and said they do exist, but so far he\rquote 
s only been able to show rather weak effects. They\rquote re significant, they\rquote re there, but the difficulty is, I think the crucial bit of data is missing, and that\rquote 
s wealth and the inter-generational transmission of wealth. The other thing that I thought you were going to say - that in many ways is another problem that we can, in principle, tackle on the basis of the cohort studies, but it\rquote 
s going to get very complicated - now is the number of kids with step-parents \'85 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
\par 
\par Anne:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 Because you don\rquote t know which household they\rquote re growing up in. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
