\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 Exactly. So this is something that is on the agenda, but we have to look, see what data we\rquote 
ve got on that. We will be able to follow through the parents who were in the original cohort, but if, say, the wife was in the original cohort, we will know, then, about her second or third husband, but the husband who wasn\rquote t in the cohort, we won
\rquote t know anything about his next wife if he found one. But what Bess Bukodi has done, and is really an extraordinary achievement, for the \rquote 46 cohort as well as the \rquote 58 and \rquote 7
0 cohort, she has really got all the basic data of family history, employment history, occupational and class history, so for every cohort member we know where they were through their lives, month by month. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
