\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 Oh yes, it\rquote s all there. It\rquote s all coded up. No, it isn\rquote t all coded up. There are some problems with the \rquote 
46 data. And especially in periods where they\rquote 
re harking back quite a long way. Not so much because there were gaps in the sweeps, but some people went missing and then they came back in and so on. In principle, all the data are there, for people who stayed in the cohorts. What we\rquote 
re also doing to try and check how serious this is in our big research project, which is on the role of education in social mobility, we\rquote 
re, right now, doing a massive multiple imputation exercise. This is a bit of statistical black magic, where you impute missing data from the data, what you know about the data you have. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
