\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 Yes. Obviously there are dangers in it, but you try and minimise these through the techniqu
e. Yes, it is a way of doing the best you can with what you\rquote ve got, and it\rquote s probably better than ignoring missing data \endash  or, at least, it\rquote 
s a check. If you use only the complete cases, then you do this multiple imputation, and you don\rquote t get very different results, then that\rquote s reassuring. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
