\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 Yes. Well, oddly enough, the difference is not as great as you might think with North London, in one way or another, because they
\rquote re all so busy, you know, and things. But on the hobbies side, one thing that helped a bit with this, one of my hobbies has always been bird watching, and Robert Erikson is a great bird watcher. So wherever we are in the world we usually take off 
\'85 And my son got
 interested in this, and he really specialises in topography and natural history books, so that comes in quite useful, because a lot of these very rare books are about birds. And then I played soccer, all the time I was in Leicester I played soccer for a 
local works team in the local Leicester League, and after having been there a few months, I had a terrific collision with the opposing goal-keeper, and broke my nose \endash 
 that was on the Saturday, and Monday morning I remember having to lecture with two magnificent black eyes! And all the kids shouting, \'93What does the other fella look like, then!\'94 (LAUGHS) And I kept playing tennis. I played regularly for King
\rquote s when I was in Cambridge, and as [for tournament] tennis from time to time I played a bit. I always played a lot of chess. Well, of course, when chess computers came in, I moved over to computer chess. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
