\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 I still play a bit of computer chess. And my other great thing is cryptic crosswords. I usually - when I\rquote ve finishe
d at the end of the day, I usually have about an hour doing the Guardian crossword, and then at the weekend, The Observer, the Azed Crossword. So that\rquote 
s the main. And we have this flat in the Barbican, so we go to a lot of concerts in the Barbican. I\rquote ve always read a lot of poetry, not so much novels, but I still read a fair bit of poetry. It was wonderful - I don\rquote 
t know whether you heard it on radio just a few weeks ago - Tony Harrison reading V. That speaks a lot to my background, of course, that poem. I\rquote m a terrific Harrison admirer. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
