\par Anne:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 Well, ... isn\rquote t it possible also to say that that was a shrewd decision, that in your own theorising it\rquote 
s the decisions individuals make in certain circumstances, which meant that you looked to Europe, and if you hadn\rquote t done that, maybe a lot of the work that you have done \endash  and that you would have rightly been called the pioneer for it 
- wouldn\rquote t have happened. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
\par 
\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 From my own point of view, I think I\rquote 
ve had a very fortunate, very happy career, and generally things have worked out very well. But it\rquote s a bit odd, I am British, but I\rquote m not, in any meaningful sense, a British sociologist. I\rquote 
m British and a sociologist, but most of what I do has very little resonance in British sociology. I\rquote ve never \endash  since the mid-seventies \endash  got very much out of British sociology, scarcely anything. The only areas where I\rquote 
ve [had] some involvement, have 
been in more interdisciplinary research centres like the Institute of Education, the Centre for Longitudinal Studies there, which is now brought together in a Faculty of Quantitative Social Science, and I felt very at home there. There\rquote 
s been a few other centres, like the Centre for Educational Sociology that David Raffe started off in Edinburgh, and some of the things that have been done \endash  not all \endash  in the interdisciplinary research centre at Essex [ISER]. But it\rquote 
s more the sociology departments, I think, where the problem is. There are some signs that it\rquote s changing, and that\rquote s my hope \endash 
 that it may. Manchester has got one or two quite good quantitative people, some developments there, although some counter-developments as well. There\rquote s just a possibility \endash  I can\rquote t say any more \endash 
 that there could be a major change at LSE, about 50-50 chance, or perhaps a bit less than 50-50, but it could be quite exciting if it happened. So there are some little green shoots, but I think it will take quite a long time. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
