\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 I didn\rquote t
 feel that, certainly. These were people I knew pretty well. No, not barbed. There is a tradition in these communities of what they call \'93kidding\'94, which means they\rquote 
re taking the mick, and I thought they saw this as a good opportunity to give me a hard time, but I didn\rquote t sense any hostility because I\rquote 
d moved out. I have to say I never encountered that at all in my local village. They were all, generally, as I said - people were very supportive, and I think, as I told you last time, I went back there all thr
ough my working life, because my mother lived to be almost 101, so I was going back there in the last few years, like every few weeks, and they were all extremely supportive and helpful. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
