they were, in some ways. They were generally people of goodwill. As long as you - I mean, I was careful never to, as it were, talk down to them. And the one problem that I had was, literally, how to talk to them \endash 
 whether to use dialect or not. I still can speak dialect, but I felt that might be a bit patronising because they would know that normally I didn\rquote 
t obviously speak dialect, so I spoke to them - I guess something in-between standard English and - obviously we\rquote d use dialect words and things like that, but not the full thing. That was the only kind of thing I found a little bit odd. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
