\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 I don\rquote t think they were all that interested \endash  not the chaps down there on the coalface, because I\rquote 
m not sure they really knew why I was down there, the people that I knew there. Of course, I did have to explain it quite fully to the managers, and especially to the trade union for the supervisory workers, which was different from the NUM \endash 
 they had their own union. But also, of course, I had to talk to the NUM people at the mine. They were all very interested and supportive, and they recognised the issue, be
cause there was this big change from semi-mechanised mining where the machines simply cut the coal, and then the miners had to load it into tubs, to machines that, as it were, both cut and loaded, and this changed the working relationships a lot. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
