\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 I\rquote m going to answer very shortly. I know some of Glen Elder\rquote s work, and I do like it. And now I\rquote 
m myself, working with the cohorts for this [project], I\rquote m very much into life course research, and I can see where having respondents\rquote 
 own accounts of their life history, could be a very valuable complement, in various ways, to the kind of quantitative analyses that we do. And as you probably know, for the \rquote 58 cohort, they were invited to write some of that. I\rquote 
ve not looked at that material yet, and I\rquote m a bit surprised that - I know Jane Elliot was planning to work on it - I\rquote ve not seen any results from it, but it could be interesting. And because of my various 
Polish connections, I know that there was this great tradition in Poland of this qualitative life history research that partly got reflected in the Thomas and Znaniecki book on The Polish Peasant. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
