\par John:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 There is a German colleague who\rquote s done fascinating work in this area, and I know his work better than Glen Elder\rquote s 
\endash  Martin Kohli. I\rquote m sure that Paul will know of his work. I think that is fascinating. I would be interested in how one could integrate it with quantitative analyses. But I\rquote m afraid on Cherlin and Furstenberg, I\rquote 
ve seen, you know, odd things by them, but I\rquote ve no great familiarity with this family research at all. I\rquote ve covered quite a few areas, but this is not one of them! (LAUGHS) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid10491433\charrsid10491433 
